      "slug": "docker-ai-redteam-arsenal",
      "titulo": "Docker: The AI Red Teamer's Secret Weapon",
      "fecha": "2026-02-01",
      "tags": ["Docker", "Red Teaming", "AI Security", "MLOps", "DevSecOps"],
      "imagen": "",
      "resumen": "Why Docker is not optional in AI Security — from isolated attack sandboxes to portable Red Team toolkits and GPU beast taming.",
      "contenido": [
        "## The Problem",
        "",
        "In the world of AI Red Teaming and ML Security, the phrase \"it works on my machine\" is a death sentence.",
        "",
        "When your job involves auditing massive language models, simulating adversary attacks, or building defenses for autonomous agents, you can't afford to waste three days wrestling with incompatible CUDA versions or Python libraries.",
        "",
        "The environment is hostile and complex. This is where Docker ceases to be a simple web deployment tool and becomes our **containment lab** and **portable arsenal**.",
        "",
        "## How I Use Docker as an AI Security Engineer",
        "",
        "I don't just use Docker to \"ship\" code. I use it to **survive the chaos**:",
        "",
        "### 1. The Sandbox for Controlled Chaos (Red Teaming)",
        "",
        "If I'm testing a prompt injection attack that could lead to Remote Code Execution (RCE) on an AI agent, I need **isolation**.",
        "",
        "Docker is my shooting range:",
        "- Launch an ephemeral container",
        "- Deploy the exploit",
        "- Observe the impact",
        "- Destroy the environment",
        "",
        "If the agent \"dies\" or does something dangerous, the damage remains **contained within the container**, without affecting my host or the corporate network.",
        "",
        "```yaml",
        "# Isolated attack network",
        "networks:",
        "  redteam:",
        "    internal: true  # No internet access",
        "",
        "services:",
        "  target-agent:",
        "    image: vulnerable-llm-agent:latest",
        "    networks: [redteam]",
        "  ",
        "  attacker:",
        "    image: my-redteam-toolkit:latest",
        "    volumes:",
        "      - ./attacks:/attacks",
        "    networks: [redteam]",
        "```",
        "",
        "### 2. Taming the GPU Beast (Infrastructure)",
        "",
        "Setting up the NVIDIA driver stack + CUDA toolkit + cuDNN + PyTorch/TensorFlow specifically for a security test is a **recurring nightmare**.",
        "",
        "With `nvidia-docker`, we standardize the testing environment:",
        "",
        "```dockerfile",
        "FROM nvidia/cuda:12.1-runtime-ubuntu22.04",
        "",
        "# One image, one CUDA version, zero headaches",
        "RUN pip install torch==2.1.0+cu121 -f https://...",
        "```",
        "",
        "The **reproducibility** of an exploit or a defense is critical for the final report.",
        "",
        "### 3. Portable Attack Toolkits",
        "",
        "My Red Teaming arsenal lives in Docker images:",
        "- Fuzzing scripts",
        "- API clients for LLMs",
        "- Toxicity analysis tools",
        "- Prompt injection payloads",
        "",
        "```bash",
        "# Arrive at new environment",
        "docker pull adrianinfantes/redteam-toolkit:latest",
        "",
        "# Swiss Army knife ready in seconds",
        "docker run -it --rm redteam-toolkit",
        "```",
        "",
        "Regardless of the underlying operating system.",
        "",
        "### 4. DevSecOps for ML Pipelines",
        "",
        "We integrate security scans directly into Docker image build stages:",
        "",
        "```dockerfile",
        "# Multi-stage with security scanning",
        "FROM python:3.11-slim AS builder",
        "COPY requirements.txt .",
        "RUN pip install -r requirements.txt",
        "",
        "# Scan for vulnerabilities",
        "FROM aquasec/trivy AS scanner",
        "COPY --from=builder /usr/local /usr/local",
        "RUN trivy filesystem --severity HIGH,CRITICAL /usr/local",
        "",
        "# Scan ML models for malware",
        "FROM builder AS model-scanner",
        "COPY models/ /models/",
        "RUN python -m modelscan scan /models/  # .pth, .safetensors",
        "```",
        "",
        "Models get scanned **before** they go into production.",
        "",
        "## Architecture Overview",
        "",
        "```",
        "┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐",
        "│              ISOLATED DOCKER NETWORK                   │",
        "│                  (internal: true)                      │",
        "│  ┌─────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────┐         │",
        "│  │  TARGET AI      │      │  RED TEAM       │         │",
        "│  │  AGENT          │◀────▶│  TOOLBOX        │         │",
        "│  │  (Victim)       │      │  (Attacker)     │         │",
        "│  │    [API]        │      │    [API]        │         │",
        "│  └────────┬────────┘      └────────┬────────┘         │",
        "│           │                        │                   │",
        "│           │    ATTACK PAYLOADS     │                   │",
        "│           │  (Fuzzing, Prompt Inj) │                   │",
        "│           └────────────────────────┘                   │",
        "└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘",
        "           │                              │",
        "           ▼                              ▼",
        "    ┌──────────────┐              ┌──────────────┐",
        "    │  GPU ACCESS  │              │ ATTACK SCRIPTS│",
        "    │  (NVIDIA)    │              │   VOLUME     │",
        "    └──────────────┘              └──────────────┘",
        "                    HOST MACHINE",
        "               (Linux / Docker Engine)",
        "```",
        "",
        "## The Bottom Line",
        "",
        "In AI Security, Docker is **not optional**.",
        "",
        "It's the difference between:",
        "- ✅ A reproducible, professional security experiment",
        "- ❌ An unmanageable mess of broken dependencies",
        "",
        "## Key Takeaways",
        "",
        "| Use Case | Docker Benefit |",
        "|----------|----------------|",
        "| Red Teaming | Isolated sandbox, ephemeral environments |",
        "| GPU Workloads | Standardized CUDA stack, reproducibility |",
        "| Toolkits | Portable arsenal, OS-agnostic |",
        "| DevSecOps | Security scans in CI/CD, model scanning |",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "*What's your biggest headache when setting up AI security testing environments that Docker has solved (or not) for you?*"
      ]
    },
