      "slug": "docker-ml-security",
      "titulo": "Hardening Docker Containers for ML Workloads",
      "fecha": "2026-01-10",
      "tags": ["Docker", "MLOps", "Security"],
      "imagen": "",
      "resumen": "Best practices for securing Docker containers in Machine Learning environments with GPU support.",
      "contenido": [
        "## Why ML Needs Special Attention",
        "",
        "ML containers have unique requirements: GPU access, large models, and often run with elevated privileges. This expands the attack surface.",
        "",
        "## Security Checklist",
        "",
        "### Base Images",
        "```dockerfile",
        "# BAD: generic image with everything",
        "FROM python:3.11",
        "",
        "# GOOD: slim or distroless image",
        "FROM python:3.11-slim-bookworm",
        "```",
        "",
        "### Non-Root User",
        "```dockerfile",
        "RUN useradd -m -u 1000 mluser",
        "USER mluser",
        "```",
        "",
        "### Read-Only Filesystem",
        "```yaml",
        "# docker-compose.yml",
        "services:",
        "  inference:",
        "    read_only: true",
        "    tmpfs:",
        "      - /tmp",
        "```",
        "",
        "### GPU Security",
        "```yaml",
        "deploy:",
        "  resources:",
        "    reservations:",
        "      devices:",
        "        - driver: nvidia",
        "          capabilities: [gpu]",
        "          # Limit to specific GPUs",
        "          device_ids: ['0']",
        "```",
        "",
        "## Vulnerability Scanning",
        "",
        "```bash",
        "# Trivy - most comprehensive for ML",
        "trivy image mymodel:latest",
        "",
        "# Grype - fast alternative",
        "grype mymodel:latest",
        "```",
        "",
        "## Secrets Management",
        "",
        "```dockerfile",
        "# NEVER do this",
        "ENV OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxx",
        "",
        "# Use BuildKit secrets",
        "RUN --mount=type=secret,id=api_key cat /run/secrets/api_key",
        "```",
        "",
        "## Conclusion",
        "",
        "Securing ML containers requires balancing performance and security. Multi-stage builds, non-root users, and continuous scanning are the minimum."
      ]
    },
